      "text": "The world witnessed it again yesterday. These are Banyamulenge, Kinyarwanda-speaking Congolese from the Democratic Republic of the Congo, many of whom have faced persecution, repeated displacement, and exile while their own government has failed to guarantee their protection.\n\nWhat is being ignored is the reality of targeted violence and ethnic cleansing affecting minority communities in North Kivu and South Kivu. While Banyamulenge communities raise their voices in Washington, D.C. and Nairobi, the United States and other international actors appear more focused on strategic interests and mineral agreements than on the fate of civilians. Villages in Minembwe and surrounding areas have faced attacks, destruction, blockade, hunger, and mass displacement from August 2025 to April 2026. The international community is failing while another atrocity against vulnerable minorities unfolds in broad daylight.",
